Write a program that accepts a number from the user.
If the number is negative, throw a custom exception NegativeNumberException.
Otherwise, print the square of the number.



OUTPUT:-
Enter any number: 5
Square is: 25

Enter any number: -5
ERROR: Number can not be negative



CODE:-
import java.util.*;

class NegativeNumberException extends Exception{
    public NegativeNumberException(String message){
        super(message);
    }
}

public class App{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter any number: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        try{
            square(n);
        }
        catch(NegativeNumberException e){
            System.out.println("ERROR: " + e.getMessage());
        }
        
    }

    static void square(int n) throws NegativeNumberException{
        if(n < 0){
            throw new NegativeNumberException("Number can not be negative");
        }
        else{
            System.out.println("Square is: " + n*n);
        }
    }
}
